overview: Set ninety-seven years after a nuclear war has destroyed civilization, when a spaceship housing humanity's lone survivors sends one hundred juvenile delinquents back to Earth, in hopes of possibly re-populating the planet.
name: The 100

episodes.overview: Ninety-seven years ago, nuclear Armageddon decimated planet Earth, destroying civilization. The only survivors were the 400 inhabitants of 12 international space stations that were in orbit at the time. Three generations have been born in space, the survivors now number 4,000, and resources are running out on their dying "Ark." Among the 100 young exiles are Clarke, the bright teenage daughter of the Ark’s chief medical officer; the daredevil Finn; the brother/sister duo of Bellamy and Octavia, whose illegal sibling status has always led them to flaunt the rules, the lighthearted Jasper and the resourceful Monty. Technologically blind to what’s happening on the planet below them, the Ark’s leaders — Clarke’s widowed mother, Abby; Chancellor Jaha; and his shadowy second in command, Kane — are faced with difficult decisions about life, death and the continued existence of the human race.
episodes.name: Pilot

episodes.overview: Having discovered that Jasper may still be alive, Clarke, Bellamy, Octavia, Finn and Monty set out on a mission to locate their friend and are shocked at what they find. Meanwhile, on the Ark, Abby is determined to get to Earth, and enlists Raven to craft an escape pod.
episodes.name: Earth Skills

episodes.overview: In a desperate attempt to treat Jasper’s festering wounds, Clarke, Finn and Wells set out in search of a seaweed antibiotic. Bellamy and his crew go hunting for food, and are joined by Charlotte, a lovable 13-year-old, who feels safe under Bellamy’s protection. A thick, acidic fog appears, forcing Clarke, Finn and Wells to seek shelter inside an ancient van. While they are trapped, Clarke confronts Wells on his betrayal that resulted in her father’s death.
episodes.name: Earth Kills

episodes.overview: After the shocking death of one of their own, Clarke and Finn grow closer as they try to figure out a way to communicate with the Ark. Bellamy must keep the group from turning on one another as life on Earth takes a desperate turn. Meanwhile, Abby risks having herself floated in order to give Raven the chance to stow-away in the escape pod bound for Earth.
episodes.name: Murphy's Law

episodes.overview: Clarke’s newfound romance with Finn is threatened. Octavia suffers a blow to the head and wakes up to find a Grounder watching her. On the Ark, Abby exposes Kane’s plan to reduce the population of the Ark. Jaha and Abby notice a signal and realize at least some of the 100 must still be alive on Earth.
episodes.name: Twilight's Last Gleaming

episodes.overview: Bellamy leads his crew into Grounder territory as they search for Octavia. Raven can't help but notice the deep connection between Finn and Clarke. Meanwhile, flashbacks reveal Bellamy's and Octavia's childhood on the Ark.
episodes.name: His Sister's Keeper

episodes.overview: Clarke and Raven make contact with the Ark, and Abby guides Clarke through a dangerous procedure in a desperate move to save one of their own. Meanwhile, on the Ark, Abby is removed from the council, and former Chancellor Diana Sydney takes her place. Jaha reveals to Abby that there are not enough drop ships for everyone on the Ark to go down to Earth, and Kane begins to deal with his guilt over his recent decision.
episodes.name: Contents Under Pressure

episodes.overview: Clarke and Bellamy go on a mission to find supplies for approaching winter. Some of the 100 accidentally eat nuts with powerfully hallucinogenic properties and lose their grasp on reality. Meanwhile, Octavia seizes the opportunity to help a friend escape, and a terrifying event brings Clarke and Bellamy closer. On the Ark, Commander Shumway secretly assigns one of the 100 to kill one of his own, and the treacherous actions of Diane Sydney are revealed.
episodes.name: Day Trip

episodes.overview: Clarke and Finn attempt to broker peace with the Grounders but all hell breaks loose when Bellamy, Jasper and Raven show up armed and ready for battle. Octavia and Lincoln grow closer. Meanwhile, tragedy strikes during the Unity Day celebration on the Ark.
episodes.name: Unity Day

episodes.overview: Murphy returns to camp claiming to have been held captive and tortured by the Grounders, and Clarke and Bellamy have very different opinions on how to handle his return. Octavia sneaks away to find Lincoln and returns with a serious warning for the 100. Meanwhile, a mysterious virus strikes camp forcing many to be quarantined, and Jasper pulls off a heroic move.
episodes.name: I Am Become Death

episodes.overview: With a low food supply at camp, Clarke and Finn lead a group out to hunt for food and wind up in a compromising position. With Finn’s life in danger, Clarke makes a game-changing decision. Meanwhile, Raven makes Bellamy an offer he can’t refuse. On the Ark – Kane risks his life and is reunited with Chancellor Jaha and Abby.
episodes.name: The Calm

episodes.overview: Clarke and Finn escape one dangerous situation only to find themselves faced with a new enemy. Bellamy makes a heroic move to save Jasper. Raven faces a new danger, and Murphy finally gets his revenge. Meanwhile, those remaining on the Ark are coming to terms with the inevitable.
episodes.name: We Are Grounders (1)

episodes.overview: Clarke pleads with Bellamy to do the right thing as conflict on the ground comes to a head. Bellamy forces Octavia to make a difficult decision. Raven and Jasper work against time and Finn makes a bold move. Meanwhile, the situation on the Ark comes to a stunning conclusion.
episodes.name: We Are Grounders (2)

episodes.overview: Clarke is still alone in the white room, frantically trying to make sense of her bizarre surroundings, while the fate of Bellamy, Finn and Raven is still unknown. Lincoln and Octavia’s daring plan is thwarted and an enemy returns. Meanwhile, Abby, Kane and the survivors of the Ark must face physical and moral dilemmas in their dangerous and beautiful new world. Finally, Jaha makes a heroic decision.
episodes.name: The 48

episodes.overview: A suspicious Clarke confronts President Dante Wallace and demands answers. Kane interrogates one of The 100, and Abby performs emergency surgery. Meanwhile, Octavia resorts to violence to find Lincoln.
episodes.name: Inclement Weather

episodes.overview: When Clarke discovers a horrifying project being carried out in Mount Weather’s medical ward, she joins forces with an unlikely ally. After Abby confesses to committing a crime, Kane issues an order to have her brutally punished. Meanwhile, Monty warns a distracted Jasper that Clarke could be in trouble, and Octavia continues to fight for Lincoln.
episodes.name: Reapercussions

episodes.overview: After being betrayed by someone she thought she could trust, Clarke takes matters into her own hands and proves she’s not going down without a flight. Bellamy, Finn and Murphy race against time to save a stranger. Meanwhile, tensions rise between Raven and Wick while working together, and an unexpected reunion occurs.
episodes.name: Many Happy Returns

episodes.overview: Kane leads a mission to make peace with the Grounders. Meanwhile, Jasper agrees to participate in a risky experiment, Lincoln enters a world of pain and President Dante Wallace issues a warning. Finally, Finn’s search for Clarke takes a violent turn.
episodes.name: Human Trials

episodes.overview: Tensions run high between Clarke and Finn, while Raven discovers that Mount Weather is interfering with their communication systems. Meanwhile, Jasper and Monty discover the truth about what’s going on at Mount Weather and Octavia comes face-to-face with her worst nightmare. Finally, President Dante Wallace is about to be betrayed by those closest to him.
episodes.name: Fog of War

episodes.overview: As Abby and Jaha each try to establish their authority, Clarke comes up with a plan to stop the Grounders' attack. At Mount Weather, Jasper, Monty, Miller and Harper plan their escape, as Dr. Tsing and Cage conduct deadly experiments.
episodes.name: Long Into an Abyss

episodes.overview: Clarke returns to Camp Jaha with devastating news. Finn struggles with the aftermath of his actions. Abby gathers information from an unlikely source and prepares for a fight. Meanwhile, flashbacks reveal Finn and Raven’s relationship on the Ark.
episodes.name: Spacewalker

episodes.overview: Clarke strikes a deal with Lexa and Indra. Abby and Kane begin to realize that decision making powers are out of their hands. A seething Raven is unable to control her emotions. A bold move threatens to destroy the newly formed alliance between the sky people and the Grounders, and a familiar face haunts Clarke. Meanwhile, back at Mount Weather, Monty comes up with a risky plan.
episodes.name: Remember Me

episodes.overview: Tensions between Clarke and Abby come to a head after Clarke crosses the line. Raven helps Bellamy navigate Mount Weather. Jaha and Murphy encounter a stranger who may not be what she seems. Octavia is prepared to fight for someone she loves. Meanwhile, things reach a breaking point at Mount Weather.
episodes.name: Rubicon

episodes.overview: While preparing for battle, Clarke and Lexa have a heated discussion. Desperate for help, Raven has Wick summoned to the engineering room. Jaha and Murphy encounter a perilous roadblock. Meanwhile, at Mount Weather, Bellamy is in a race against time.
episodes.name: Bodyguard of Lies

episodes.overview: Lives are at risk as Clarke and Lexa encounter a new enemy. Bellamy and Lincoln agree to work together to break into Mount Weather. Murphy helps Jaha confront his past. Meanwhile, Indra makes Octavia an offer she can’t refuse.
episodes.name: Survival of the Fittest

episodes.overview: Bellamy and Lincoln’s attempt to sneak into Mount Weather has brutal consequences. Abby fights to stay in control as Clarke steps up in her new leadership role. Meanwhile, with Monty and Harper still missing, a desperate Jasper confronts President Wallace and demands answers.
episodes.name: Coup de Grâce

episodes.overview: Clarke begins to question Lexa’s leadership decisions. Abby struggles to help an injured Kane. Indra continues to push Octavia. Meanwhile, at Mount Weather, Jasper steps up into the role of leader, and Cage throws Maya into a life threatening situation.
episodes.name: Resurrection

episodes.overview: Clarke and Lexa prepare for battle, while Raven and Wick experience a major setback. Meanwhile, Octavia and Lincoln are each forced to make a difficult decision. At Mount Weather, Jasper and Maya witness a horrible act, Bellamy follows through on a promise and Cage goes public with powerful information.
episodes.name: Blood Must Have Blood (1)

episodes.overview: The journey to the City of Light continues, and Jaha makes a move that shocks Murphy. Clarke receives help from an unexpected source, a visitor surprises Octavia, and Lincoln gets his revenge. Meanwhile, at Mount Weather, Cage moves forward with his mission and Bellamy and the group struggle to break free.
episodes.name: Blood Must Have Blood (2)

episodes.overview: Three months have passed since the tragedy at Mount Weather and our heroes learn that a bounty has been put on Clarke’s head. Unbeknownst to Clarke, a team led by Bellamy and Kane journeys deep into Grounder territory to save her. Meanwhile, Murphy finds his way to the mansion and discovers a very different Jaha on a very different mission.
episodes.name: Wanheda (1)

episodes.overview: Bellamy and Kane risk life and limb to rescue Clarke. In an attempt to avoid worrying about her daughter, Abby focuses on whether to open Mount Weather as a medical facility. Murphy plots to betray his former Chancellor.
episodes.name: Wanheda (2)

episodes.overview: Clarke wrestles with a decision. Bellamy learns that something isn't what it seems. Murphy plots to betray his former Chancellor.
episodes.name: Ye Who Enter Here

episodes.overview: Clarke discovers the mastermind behind a devious plan. Kane struggles to keep the peace. Meanwhile, Jasper’s grief drives him to reckless behavior.
episodes.name: Watch the Thrones

episodes.overview: Pike's twisted crusade threatens Clarke's attempts for peace. Raven becomes a target. Murphy tries to conspire against Jaha.
episodes.name: Hakeldama

episodes.overview: Clarke is torn between vengeance and mercy. Kane and Octavia work together to avert a disaster. Abby continues to worry about Raven.
episodes.name: Bitter Harvest

episodes.overview: Lexa tries to maintain peace and order within the clans. Clarke uncovers a strange and game-changing truth. A flashback takes us into the darker chapter of humanity’s past.
episodes.name: Thirteen

episodes.overview: Kane searches for a peaceful way to handle things but soon realizes he may be forced to resort to drastic measures. Pike suspects that there may be a leak within the walls of Arkadia. Raven has a plan and reaches out to Jasper for help.
episodes.name: Terms and Conditions

episodes.overview: Clarke discovers a shocking truth. Octavia is forced to make a decision that could have devastating consequences. Kane and Abby share a moment.
episodes.name: Stealing Fire

episodes.overview: Jaha employs a terrifying new method to convince Abby to join his cause, Kane is on a mission. Bellamy is hit with a hard truth. Monty finds himself in a precarious situation. Jasper rushes to save one of his own.
episodes.name: Fallen

episodes.overview: Alie forces Raven’s dark side to come out. Jasper’s anger continues to grow. Octavia wrestles with her place in the world. Monty is forced to make a split-second decision.
episodes.name: Nevermore

episodes.overview: Jaha returns to Polis. Murphy has a surprise encounter. Octavia uncovers a clue.
episodes.name: Demons

episodes.overview: Clarke is on a mission that could change everything. Murphy gains insight that might prove useful in ensuring his survival. Kane reaches a breaking point.
episodes.name: Join or Die

episodes.overview: Clarke, Bellamy, Octavia, and Jasper hit a tragic roadblock. Raven and Monty make an important discovery.
episodes.name: Red Sky at Morning

episodes.overview: Clarke finds hope in the most unlikely place. Alie’s master plan comes together.
episodes.name: Perverse Instantiation (1)

episodes.overview: Our heroes begin to face the reality of their tragic situation. Everyone prepares for a final showdown.
episodes.name: Perverse Instantiation (2)

episodes.overview: Clarke and her friends struggle with how to proceed after the fate of the world is revealed.
episodes.name: Echoes

episodes.overview: The burden of leading weighs heavily upon Clarke and Bellamy when different challenges force them to determine who will live and die.
episodes.name: Heavy Lies The Crown

episodes.overview: Jaha leads Clarke and Bellamy down a road to possible salvation while tensions rise in Arkadia and Polis.
episodes.name: The Four Horsemen

episodes.overview: Continued struggles with leadership and trust in Arkadia and Polis take violent turns while Abby leads a team to a distant location hoping to find answers.
episodes.name: A Lie Guarded

episodes.overview: Clarke makes a desperate plea with a former allied force in an attempt to avoid a war and ensure the survival of her people.
episodes.name: The Tinder Box

episodes.overview: Clarke and Roan must work together in hostile territory in order to deliver an invaluable asset to Abby and her team.
episodes.name: We Will Rise

episodes.overview: Clarke’s arrival on the island quickly takes a turn for the worse. Meanwhile, Bellamy tries to avoid further tragedy in Arkadia.
episodes.name: Gimme Shelter

episodes.overview: It's a race against the end of the world as Praimfaya arrives forcing our heroes to make impossible decisions to ensure their survival.
episodes.name: Praimfaya

episodes.overview: After a disappointing discovery, Clarke and Abby question how far they're willing to go. Meanwhile, Jaha finds a lead to the mysterious Second Dawn.
episodes.name: God Complex

episodes.overview: Clarke faces the consequences of her fateful choice.
episodes.name: The Other Side

episodes.overview: Jasper and Bellamy go on a quest. Meanwhile, Clarke struggles to keep the peace after word of Jaha's discovery spreads.
episodes.name: DNR

episodes.overview: Jaha and Kane disagree over how to handle their grim reality. Meanwhile, Clarke leads a group to save a friend.
episodes.name: The Chosen

episodes.overview: Octavia fights in the final battle for her people's survival, but not everyone is willing to play fair.
episodes.name: Die All, Die Merrily

episodes.overview: Clarke struggles to survive on a desolate, scorched earth while her friends in space come across a long-awaited beacon of hope.
episodes.name: Eden

episodes.overview: Bellamy leads the charge investigating a potential way home. Meanwhile, Clarke and Madi deal with the new, uncertain threat to their home.
episodes.name: Sleeping Giants

episodes.overview: Octavia is forced to take guidance from an unlikely ally when the future of the bunker and all those inside it is jeopardized.
episodes.name: Red Queen

episodes.overview: Our Heroes are forced to rely on the help of Shallow Valley's dangerous new inhabitants in order to save some of their own, with surprising results.
episodes.name: Pandora's Box

episodes.overview: Octavia leads her people towards Shallow Valley against the advice of Clarke and Bellamy. Meanwhile, Kane and Abby adjust to a new set of challenges.
episodes.name: Shifting Sands

episodes.overview: Clarke and Bellamy make a startling discovery about Wonkru’s battle plans as Echo risks her friendship with Raven to complete her mission.
episodes.name: Acceptable Losses

episodes.overview: The growing fractures in Wonkru threaten to explode once and for all. Meanwhile, in Shallow Valley, Murphy starts a fire, unleashing catastrophic results.
episodes.name: Sic Semper Tyrannis

episodes.overview: Monty strives to show Wonkru an alternative to war, and to the valley itself. Meanwhile, Abby’s health continues to deteriorate, along with McCreary’s patience.
episodes.name: The Warriors Will

episodes.overview: As Clarke races to save Abby, she learns more about the trials and tribulations Wonkru faced in the bunker, and the impossible decisions they were forced to make in the dark year.
episodes.name: The Dark Year

episodes.overview: In part one of the fifth season finale, Octavia leads her people into war. While behind enemy lines, our heroes must overcome their differences to save Wonkru from extinction.
episodes.name: Damocles (1)

episodes.overview: In part two of the fifth season finale, Clarke and her friends must risk everything to fight one last battle for survival, only to glimpse an even darker threat to the last living valley on Earth.
episodes.name: Damocles (2)

episodes.overview: Kane’s attempt to prove himself useful tests Wonkru’s allegiance to Octavia. Madi faces an unexpected threat inside Wonkru, forcing Clarke to make an unlikely ally.
episodes.name: Exit Wounds

episodes.overview: Clarke’s determination to protect Madi puts Bellamy in an impossible position.
episodes.name: How We Get to Peace

episodes.overview: Still reeling after receiving Monty’s message, a small group goes down to explore the mysterious new planet. Back on the Mothership, several members of Wonkru face the consequences of their decisions.
episodes.name: Sanctum

episodes.overview: The team on the ground fights to survive the threat they face on the new planet. Meanwhile, Raven must join forces with an unlikely ally to save everyone on board the mothership.
episodes.name: Red Sun Rising

episodes.overview: Clarke tries to win over the leaders of Sanctum in order to let her people stay. Meanwhile, Bellamy, Echo and Octavia discover a new threat while on a mission to retrieve the transport ship.
episodes.name: The Children of Gabriel

episodes.overview: Clarke embraces the traditions of Sanctum and tries to make amends for her past actions.
episodes.name: The Face Behind the Glass

episodes.overview: Jordan investigates Sanctum. Meanwhile, Octavia and Diyoza discover the threats of the new planet firsthand. Lastly, Bellamy and Clarke butt heads.
episodes.name: The Gospel of Josephine

episodes.overview: Diyoza learns more about the mysterious Children of Gabriel while Abby continues searching for a way to save Kane.
episodes.name: Memento Mori

episodes.overview: Clarke’s past catches up to her.
episodes.name: Nevermind

episodes.overview: Octavia and Diyoza make their way to the mysterious anomaly in search of the Old Man. Meanwhile, Murphy has an offer for Emori.
episodes.name: The Old Man and the Anomaly

episodes.overview: Bellamy must venture into enemy territory with an unlikely companion. Meanwhile, Octavia is forced to confront her past.
episodes.name: What You Take With You

episodes.overview: Russell seeks justice. Meanwhile, Gabriel must make a difficult choice. Lastly, the Blake siblings reunite.
episodes.name: Matryoshka

episodes.overview: Bellamy and Octavia must work together to save their friends. Echo is forced to face her past.
episodes.name: Ashes to Ashes

episodes.overview: A special Naming Day changes everything in Sanctum. Gabriel comes face to face with an old friend.
episodes.name: Adjustment Protocol

episodes.overview: Sanctum becomes a battleground between the devout and the non-believers. The mystery of the anomaly deepens.
episodes.name: The Blood of Sanctum

episodes.overview: Clarke and her friends attempt to rebuild Sanctum as a new threat rises in the woods.
episodes.name: From the Ashes

episodes.overview: Echo and Gabriel learn more about Hope and her mysterious past.
episodes.name: The Garden

episodes.overview: Raven faces an unexpected threat. Clarke must keep the peace among opposing factions in Sanctum.
episodes.name: False Gods

episodes.overview: Mysterious outsiders arrive with news of Clarke's missing people.
episodes.name: Hesperides

episodes.overview: Octavia gets to know a whole new world. Meanwhile, Murphy and Emori play make believe.
episodes.name: Welcome to Bardo

episodes.overview: Clarke and her friends find themselves on a planet that is not what it seems.
episodes.name: Nakara

episodes.overview: Emori tries to heal Sanctum's old familial wounds while Echo, Octavia and Diyoza struggle with new ones.
episodes.name: The Queen's Gambit

episodes.overview: Clarke confronts a new adversary. A surprising connection takes us back to the past and to the nuclear apocalypse that destroyed the Earth.
episodes.name: Anaconda

episodes.overview: Murphy and Indra must defuse a tense situation. Old friends make new allegiances.
episodes.name: The Flock

episodes.overview: Sheidheda makes his move. A Disciple goes rogue.
episodes.name: A Little Sacrifice

episodes.overview: Where in the universe is Bellamy Blake?
episodes.name: Etherea

episodes.overview: Clarke and her friends reckon with all that has happened only to find an unexpected threat looming.
episodes.name: A Sort of Homecoming

episodes.overview: Clarke and Octavia mount a desperate rescue mission as the Disciples close in on what they want.
episodes.name: The Dying of the Light

episodes.overview: After all the fighting and loss, Clarke and her friends have reached the final battle. But is humanity worthy of something greater?
episodes.name: The Last War

episodes.overview: It's a new day in Sanctum. Clarke, Octavia, Raven and Echo struggle with a new foe.
episodes.name: The Stranger

episodes.overview: The red sun derails Clarke's plans.
episodes.name: Blood Giant
